To establish a clean baseline, we excluded all unmodified out-of-the-box files so what remains in our analysis is exclusively our customizations: modified OOTB files and net-new custom code.
In the Technical Debt report, you can see each file carries a clear severity rating, a classification flag Custom, OOTB-Modified, or Unresolved for files not found in the base code along with a concrete action plan for each finding.
In the Cloud Standards Violation report, you'll find the same structure, with one addition: Lines of Code per file, giving you an at-a-glance measure of the change surface for every modified or custom file.
Finally, the third report captures all the unmodified out-of-the-box files, the ones that were scanned but intentionally excluded from remediation scope. As you can see, these are clean baseline files with no dependency on our customizations, which is precisely why they fall outside our analysis boundary.
This three-report structure gives you complete traceability, what we remediate, how we classify it, and what we consciously exclude and why.
